		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Stats / Damage  Discussion: Caution - long post!<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Oct 4th 12:01 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=100221127788447&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=100221127788447&post=1&replyto=100221127788447"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=100221127788447></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.66]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Dear All,<br><br>Some info on damage for discussion / dismissal:<br><br>Strength effects three main areas; the load one may carry without being encumbered, the ATK (or attack) rating and finally the 'range' or 'bandwidth' of damage inflicted on a successful hit.<br><br>ATK consists of three things: STR, Offense and a weapon skill. Since Offense and the cap (or peak) for weapon skill is directly related to level, you can summarise this by saying 'level is a great determinant of success in combat'. But then we all knew that already! :-)<br><br>Thus, in order to hit a mob, a calculation based on a characters ATK vs a mobs AC is performed.<br><br>However, when selecting equipment, for your early stages of life (levels 1 - 30) you should focus on AC, STR then hps. Past 30th and one should begin to consider AC, hps then STR as those you group with are able to cast better STR buffs.<br><br>Post 46, and every raid-worthy paladin should start picking up resist gear. A dragon who wants to hit you, WILL hit you no matter your AC. However, having that 150 resist fire will protect you from that terrible 500dmg AoE spell...<br><br>Other stats have less of an impact, but are still important nonetheless. AGI should ALWAYS and MUST be over 75. Having an AGI of 100 is ideal but not essential. If your AGI drops below 75 you will notice a massive deficiency of AC. NEVER let your AGI go below 75. AGI is also the key stat for improvement of defensive combat skills (eg Dodge, Parry)<br><br>DEX is a well-discussed topic. As far as tests have proven, DEX is a direct factor of causing critical hits, improvement of offensive combat skills (incl. riposte, disarm, bash, kick) and the rate of weapon 'proc'.<br><br>STA is well-disputed also. Having STA over 100 will negate any effect of your 'yellow stamina bar' if it fades to nothing. STA directly impacts hps, although at low levels the effect is minimised. Young pallies are encouraged to go for +hp gear, rather than +STA gear until around level 30. One observation not often noticed by many, is that having a high STA effects how likely you're stunned by a physical Bash / Slam from a mob.<br><br>Melee classes receive a damage bonus based on level.<br><br>This can be calculated approximately using this formula for characters up to 50:<br><br>(character level - 25) / 3 <br><br>and rounded down<br><br>Thus, a 31st level char will receive a bonus of 2 damage with every hit that connects.<br><br>A 50th level char will receive a bonus of 8 damage per hit that connects.<br><br>As you can see, the lower the delay of a weapon, the more damage you will inflict. This is why dual-wielding classes with low delay weapons, often take the Taunt and favour using the 1H-type weapons at later levels.<br><br>Of course pallys have great agro-management tools, in the form of Stuns, Roots, undead Fears and even Flash of Light.<br><br>The upcoming melee changes on Test feature an increased minimum damage for 2H weapons. Currently, 2H weapons receive a damage bonus based on their delay. It's suspected that this is 1 point for every 2 delay past 30, although this is unconfirmed.<br><br>Good luck with your travels, friends.<br><br>Leolus<br>Paladin of Quellious</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
